{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"agent_message","text":"The behavior split is clearer now. `maven-gpg-plugin:1.6` uses a reflective console path with a Java 1.5 fallback, and that survives native testing; `3.0.1` changed to a direct `System.console().readPassword()` call with no fallback, so the old test technique is no longer reliable in native-image even though the resource failure is definitely a metadata gap. I’m looking for an existing repo pattern for this kind of direct-console native test before I edit anything."}}
